title: Alex Strand
link_one: A reactjs/express app that gives you a random submission from r/dailyprogrammer
link_two: Pulls data from a json file that then constructs this static site, using Rust
link_three: An android app that pulls data from json files, for all patterns in ITF Taekwondo
link_four: Grabs data from the reddit api, allows user to view wallpapers from r/wallpapers
content: My name is Alex Strand and I am currently working as a Web Developer. I play trombone, guitar and also practice Taekwondo. On the front end, I love working with  React, Styled Components, and Redux. On the backend side of things,  I'm using Java/Kotlin(for Android App development) and Rust.
